I used to rave about this place to anyone that would listen for years. Despite the fact that something always had to be messed up with the order, the flavors were fabulous. Now they are using mozzarella cheese in the burritos. Huh? When I want mozzarella I order a pizza. As a native San Diegan, I want Mexican cheese with my Mexican food. Not only did I ask what the deal was with the cheese, I was yelled at for being upset. This place has probably the best salsa in bay ridge but what a disappointment the food has become. They wouldn’t give me a refund- fine by me, I’ll never order from here again. What a real shame.

Exploring neighborhoods is a prime example of finding hidden treasure. Was looking for a place to eat and happened upon this wonderful gem. Cash only caught my eye (which is a great sign that money isn't not being wasted paying those credit card fees issued to businesses for their customer's convenience). Ordered the Molcajete platter with chicken, chorizo, skirt steak, pork chop and nopales (cactus..I had never before but oh yes will again. ((tastes like bell pepper)). This comes with warm tortillas rice and black beans and for some crunch < a major food group...lol> ordered two tostadas. This meal was extremely tasty and spicy in that lip tingly way.. oh yeaaa. So please Go and Enjoy!

Delicious food, so far a fan! Really glad to have found this neighborhood spot for enchiladas verdes. I can’t speak for dining in experience, however I’m satisfied with delivery and it’s found a spot in my regular rotation.  I love that their burritos come with fries and salad! The dressing is light in taste and texture and compliments the lettuce. Nachos con carne is decadent, it’s comes in a beautiful circle like a pizza, with a healthy dose of toppings.  I always end up overeating since the portions are generous and yum. Everything smells divine.
Probably the best Mexican food I have ever had. Their quesadilla is the best around!

Excellent, authentic Mexican food expertly prepared and humbly presented; in an elegant yet rustic fashion.  We will be back!  I had the pork pozole and my party had tacos quesadillas and guacamole.  The salsa were super fresh and varying degrees of spiciness showcasing the diverse and flavorful ingredients.  I could eat here every week.  So good!
